title: Shopify Pricing | What is Shopify? | Shopify Website | E-commerce | Shopify Tutorial

Shopify Pricing | What is Shopify? | Shopify Website | E-commerce | Shopify Tutorial

https://profiletree.com/ecommerce-web-design-agency/

Welcome to this ProfileTree video
In this video, we will explain what Shopify pricing plans are available for you to choose from and how you can build and use a website using the eCommerce platform for your own business.

Shopify is an e-commerce platform that allows individuals and businesses to create their own online stores and sell products or services online. It was founded in 2004 and has since grown to become one of the most popular e-commerce platforms in the world. 

Shopify offers several pricing plans that cater to businesses of different sizes and needs. Here are the different Shopify pricing plans and their benefits:

Basic Shopify - $29 per month: This plan is designed for small businesses just starting out with an online store. It includes all the essential features needed to launch a basic online store, including unlimited products, 24/7 customer support, and the ability to accept credit card payments.

Shopify - $79 per month: This plan includes all the features of Basic Shopify, plus more advanced features such as gift cards, professional reports, and the ability to create discount codes. It's a good option for growing businesses with higher sales volumes.

Advanced Shopify - $299 per month: This plan includes all the features of Shopify, plus more advanced features such as advanced report building, third-party calculated shipping rates, and the ability to customize your checkout process. It's ideal for large businesses with high sales volumes and complex needs.

Shopify Plus - Custom pricing: This is the most advanced plan offered by Shopify, designed for enterprise-level businesses with complex needs. It includes all the features of Advanced Shopify, plus personalized support, advanced security features, and custom integrations.

The benefits of Shopify pricing plans include:

Scalability: As your business grows and your needs change, you can upgrade your Shopify plan to access more features and support.

Flexibility: Shopify pricing plans offer flexibility to businesses of different sizes and budgets, with plans designed for small, medium, and large businesses.

Ease of use: Shopify is easy to set up and use, with an intuitive interface and a wide range of apps and integrations available to extend the platform's functionality.

Reliability: Shopify offers reliable hosting, security, and uptime, ensuring that your online store is always available to customers.

Support: Shopify offers 24/7 customer support via phone, email, and live chat, as well as a comprehensive knowledge base and community forums.

Overall, Shopify pricing plans offer a wide range of features and support to help businesses of all sizes launch and grow their online stores.

title: oToGuard - The World's First All in one ADAS System for Large Commercial Vehicles
description:
oToGuard is equipped with 1 automotive-grade ECU system, 8 cameras, and vision-Al deep learning technology. The vision-Al algorithm can detect and classify different kinds of vehicles/pedestrian/two-wheeler riders/lane marking and other objects for different purpose.
With 2 front-view cameras, it supports FCW, LDW, MOIS (UN R159) ADAS functions from 0~100 meters without blind spots. With 4 sideview cameras, it supports BSIS (UN R151) to protect vulnerable road users, especially pedestrian and two-wheeler riders within 40 meters without blind spot. With 1 rear view camera, it can support REIS (UN R158) and combine with other cameras mentioned above to support AV/M as well. With 1 in-cabin IR camera, the vision-Al algorithm can recognize over 50 drivers' identification and categorize over 10 kinds of driving status. Furthermore, its less than 20 centimeter high-precision lane detection can operate on straight and curve roads with a radius over 120m which allows the vehicle to enable level 2+ ADAS functions such as ACC, AEB, LCA, LKA, etc.

description:
A long time in the making ğŸ¥¹ Ed Sheeran has been an artist that we've admired since the day that we started Mahogany in 2009. Earlier this year Ed's team reached out to Mahogany to discuss creating a series of live performance videos for the new album '-' (Subtract) which would see us produce 8 videos in a single day including solo performances as well as with as 12-piece band led by the albums producer Aaron Dessner (The National, Taylor Swift). The whole album has a nautical and coastal theme so we chose the epic Historic Dockyard in Chatham Kent as the location - and the first video of the day was a classic single-shot Mahogany Session of 'Eyes Closed'. title: Deploy your SSH Key for IntelÂ® VTuneâ„¢ Profiler | Intel Software
description:
Intel VTune Profiler can collect workload performance data locally or on a remote target. In this video we show how to configure remote data collection on a remote Linux* target. This includes setup and creation of a trusted SSH based communication channel.

The first time you start the Intel VTune Profiler graphical user interface, create a project and then click the configure analysis button in the menu or in the welcome tab.

To configure a remote Linux* target system, mouse click in the Where Pane and select Remote Linux.

Specify the user name and network name or IP address of the target system.

VTune Profiler communicates with the target system with passwordless SSH using a private / public key pair.
If this is not already set up, VTune Profiler creates the key pair in the user's home .ssh directory and deploys the public key to the target system's authorized keys file in the home .ssh directory.

Click the Deploy button to install the data collection drivers on the target system.

On the target system, VTune Profiler creates or appends the authorized keys file in the user's home .ssh 
directory and installs the data collection drivers in the temp vtune profiler target directory.

The data collection driver source code is in the sepdk src subdirectory, with some useful scripts to rebuild and reload the drivers, and query the current driver status.
